4561 void SwitchInst::init(Value *Value, BasicBlock *Default, unsigned NumReserved) { 0
4562 assert(Value && Default && NumReserved); 0
4563 ReservedSpace = NumReserved; 0
4564 setNumHungOffUseOperands(2); 0
4565 allocHungoffUses(ReservedSpace); 0
4566 ----
4567 Op<0>() = Value; 0
4568 Op<1>() = Default; 0
4569 } 0
4570 ----
4571 /// SwitchInst ctor - Create a new switch instruction, specifying a value to ----
4572 /// switch on and a default destination. The number of additional cases can ----
4573 /// be specified here to make memory allocation more efficient. This ----
4574 /// constructor can also autoinsert before another instruction. ----
4575 SwitchInst::SwitchInst(Value *Value, BasicBlock *Default, unsigned NumCases, 0
4576 Instruction *InsertBefore) ----
4577 : Instruction(Type::getVoidTy(Value->getContext()), Instruction::Switch, ----
4578 nullptr, 0, InsertBefore) { 0
4579 init(Value, Default, 2+NumCases*2); 0
4580 } 0
4581 ----
4582 /// SwitchInst ctor - Create a new switch instruction, specifying a value to ----
4583 /// switch on and a default destination. The number of additional cases can ----
4584 /// be specified here to make memory allocation more efficient. This ----
4585 /// constructor also autoinserts at the end of the specified BasicBlock. ----
4586 SwitchInst::SwitchInst(Value *Value, BasicBlock *Default, unsigned NumCases, 0
4587 BasicBlock *InsertAtEnd) ----
4588 : Instruction(Type::getVoidTy(Value->getContext()), Instruction::Switch, ----
4589 nullptr, 0, InsertAtEnd) { 0
4590 init(Value, Default, 2+NumCases*2); 0
4591 } 0
4592 ----
4593 SwitchInst::SwitchInst(const SwitchInst &SI) 0
4594 : Instruction(SI.getType(), Instruction::Switch, nullptr, 0) { 0
4595 init(SI.getCondition(), SI.getDefaultDest(), SI.getNumOperands()); 0
4596 setNumHungOffUseOperands(SI.getNumOperands()); 0
4597 Use *OL = getOperandList(); 0
4598 const Use *InOL = SI.getOperandList(); 0
4599 for (unsigned i = 2, E = SI.getNumOperands(); i != E; i += 2) { 0
4600 OL[i] = InOL[i]; 0
4601 OL[i+1] = InOL[i+1]; 0
4602 } ----
4603 SubclassOptionalData = SI.SubclassOptionalData; 0
4604 } 0
4605 ----
4606 /// addCase - Add an entry to the switch instruction... ----
4607 /// ----
4608 void SwitchInst::addCase(ConstantInt *OnVal, BasicBlock *Dest) { 0
4609 unsigned NewCaseIdx = getNumCases(); 0
4610 unsigned OpNo = getNumOperands(); 0
4611 if (OpNo+2 > ReservedSpace) 0
4612 growOperands(); // Get more space! 0
4613 // Initialize some new operands. ----
4614 assert(OpNo+1 < ReservedSpace && "Growing didn't work!"); 0
4615 setNumHungOffUseOperands(OpNo+2); 0
4616 CaseHandle Case(this, NewCaseIdx); 0
4617 Case.setValue(OnVal); 0
4618 Case.setSuccessor(Dest); 0
4619 } 0
4620 ----
4621 /// removeCase - This method removes the specified case and its successor ----
4622 /// from the switch instruction. ----
4623 SwitchInst::CaseIt SwitchInst::removeCase(CaseIt I) { 0
4624 unsigned idx = I->getCaseIndex(); 0
4625 ----
4626 assert(2 + idx*2 < getNumOperands() && "Case index out of range!!!"); 0
4627 ----
4628 unsigned NumOps = getNumOperands(); 0
4629 Use *OL = getOperandList(); 0
4630 ----
4631 // Overwrite this case with the end of the list. ----
4632 if (2 + (idx + 1) * 2 != NumOps) { 0
4633 OL[2 + idx * 2] = OL[NumOps - 2]; 0
4634 OL[2 + idx * 2 + 1] = OL[NumOps - 1]; 0
4635 } ----
4636 ----
4637 // Nuke the last value. ----
4638 OL[NumOps-2].set(nullptr); 0
4639 OL[NumOps-2+1].set(nullptr); 0
4640 setNumHungOffUseOperands(NumOps-2); 0
4641 ----
4642 return CaseIt(this, idx); 0
4643 } ----
4644 ----
4645 /// growOperands - grow operands - This grows the operand list in response ----
4646 /// to a push_back style of operation. This grows the number of ops by 3 times. ----
4647 /// ----
4648 void SwitchInst::growOperands() { 0
4649 unsigned e = getNumOperands(); 0
4650 unsigned NumOps = e*3; 0
4651 ----
4652 ReservedSpace = NumOps; 0
4653 growHungoffUses(ReservedSpace); 0
4654 } 0
4655 ----
4656 MDNode *SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::buildProfBranchWeightsMD() { 0
4657 assert(Changed && "called only if metadata has changed"); 0
4658 ----
4659 if (!Weights) 0
4660 return nullptr; 0
4661 ----
4662 assert(SI.getNumSuccessors() == Weights->size() && 0
4663 "num of prof branch_weights must accord with num of successors"); ----
4664 ----
4665 bool AllZeroes = all_of(*Weights, [](uint32_t W) { return W == 0; }); 0
4666 ----
4667 if (AllZeroes || Weights->size() < 2) 0
4668 return nullptr; 0
4669 ----
4670 return MDBuilder(SI.getParent()->getContext()).createBranchWeights(*Weights); 0
4671 } ----
4672 ----
4673 void SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::init() { 0
4674 MDNode *ProfileData = getBranchWeightMDNode(SI); 0
4675 if (!ProfileData) 0
4676 return; 0
4677 ----
4678 if (ProfileData->getNumOperands() != SI.getNumSuccessors() + 1) { 0
4679 llvm_unreachable("number of prof branch_weights metadata operands does " 0
4680 "not correspond to number of succesors"); ----
4681 } ----
4682 ----
4683 SmallVector Weights; 0
4684 if (!extractBranchWeights(ProfileData, Weights)) 0
4685 return; 0
4686 this->Weights = std::move(Weights); 0
4687 } 0
4688 ----
4689 SwitchInst::CaseIt ----
4690 SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::removeCase(SwitchInst::CaseIt I) { 0
4691 if (Weights) { 0
4692 assert(SI.getNumSuccessors() == Weights->size() && 0
4693 "num of prof branch_weights must accord with num of successors"); ----
4694 Changed = true; 0
4695 // Copy the last case to the place of the removed one and shrink. ----
4696 // This is tightly coupled with the way SwitchInst::removeCase() removes ----
4697 // the cases in SwitchInst::removeCase(CaseIt). ----
4698 (*Weights)[I->getCaseIndex() + 1] = Weights->back(); 0
4699 Weights->pop_back(); 0
4700 } ----
4701 return SI.removeCase(I); 0
4702 } ----
4703 ----
4704 void SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::addCase( 0
4705 ConstantInt *OnVal, BasicBlock *Dest, ----
4706 SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::CaseWeightOpt W) { ----
4707 SI.addCase(OnVal, Dest); 0
4708 ----
4709 if (!Weights && W && *W) { 0
4710 Changed = true; 0
4711 Weights = SmallVector(SI.getNumSuccessors(), 0); 0
4712 (*Weights)[SI.getNumSuccessors() - 1] = *W; 0
4713 } else if (Weights) { 0
4714 Changed = true; 0
4715 Weights->push_back(W.value_or(0)); 0
4716 } ----
4717 if (Weights) 0
4718 assert(SI.getNumSuccessors() == Weights->size() && 0
4719 "num of prof branch_weights must accord with num of successors"); ----
4720 } 0
4721 ----
4722 SymbolTableList::iterator ----
4723 SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::eraseFromParent() { 0
4724 // Instruction is erased. Mark as unchanged to not touch it in the destructor. ----
4725 Changed = false; 0
4726 if (Weights) 0
4727 Weights->resize(0); 0
4728 return SI.eraseFromParent(); 0
4729 } ----
4730 ----
4731 SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::CaseWeightOpt ----
4732 SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::getSuccessorWeight(unsigned idx) { 0
4733 if (!Weights) 0
4734 return std::nullopt; 0
4735 return (*Weights)[idx]; 0
4736 } ----
4737 ----
4738 void SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::setSuccessorWeight( 0
4739 unsigned idx, SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::CaseWeightOpt W) { ----
4740 if (!W) 0
4741 return; 0
4742 ----
4743 if (!Weights && *W) 0
4744 Weights = SmallVector(SI.getNumSuccessors(), 0); 0
4745 ----
4746 if (Weights) { 0
4747 auto &OldW = (*Weights)[idx]; 0
4748 if (*W != OldW) { 0
4749 Changed = true; 0
4750 OldW = *W; 0
4751 } ----
4752 } ----
4753 } ----
4754 ----
4755 SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::CaseWeightOpt ----
4756 SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::getSuccessorWeight(const SwitchInst &SI, 0
4757 unsigned idx) { ----
4758 if (MDNode *ProfileData = getBranchWeightMDNode(SI)) 0
4759 if (ProfileData->getNumOperands() == SI.getNumSuccessors() + 1) 0
4760 return mdconst::extract(ProfileData->getOperand(idx + 1)) ----
4761 ->getValue() 0
4762 .getZExtValue(); 0
4763 ----
4764 return std::nullopt; 0
4765 } ----

4830 /// removeDestination - This method removes the specified successor from the ----
4831 /// indirectbr instruction. ----

4834 ----
4835 unsigned NumOps = getNumOperands(); 0
4836 Use *OL = getOperandList(); 0
4837 ----
4838 // Replace this value with the last one. ----
4839 OL[idx+1] = OL[NumOps-1]; 0

4842 OL[NumOps-1].set(nullptr); 0
4843 setNumHungOffUseOperands(NumOps-1); 0
4844 } 0

4440 4440
4441 bool FCmpInst::compare(const APFloat &LHS, const APFloat &RHS, 4441 bool FCmpInst::compare(const APFloat &LHS, const APFloat &RHS,
4442 FCmpInst::Predicate Pred) { 4442 FCmpInst::Predicate Pred) {
4443 APFloat::cmpResult R = LHS.compare(RHS); 4443 APFloat::cmpResult R = LHS.compare(RHS);
4444 switch (Pred) { 4444 switch (Pred) {
4445 default: 4445 default:
4446 llvm_unreachable("Invalid FCmp Predicate"); 4446 llvm_unreachable("Invalid FCmp Predicate");
4447 case FCmpInst::FCMP_FALSE: 4447 case FCmpInst::FCMP_FALSE:
4448 return false; 4448 return false;
4449 case FCmpInst::FCMP_TRUE: 4449 case FCmpInst::FCMP_TRUE:
4450 return true; 4450 return true;
4451 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO: 4451 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO:
4452 return R == APFloat::cmpUnordered; 4452 return R == APFloat::cmpUnordered;
4453 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD: 4453 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD:
4454 return R != APFloat::cmpUnordered; 4454 return R != APFloat::cmpUnordered;
4455 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UEQ: 4455 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UEQ:
4456 return R == APFloat::cmpUnordered || R == APFloat::cmpEqual; 4456 return R == APFloat::cmpUnordered || R == APFloat::cmpEqual;
4457 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ: 4457 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ:
4458 return R == APFloat::cmpEqual; 4458 return R == APFloat::cmpEqual;
4459 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE: 4459 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE:
4460 return R != APFloat::cmpEqual; 4460 return R != APFloat::cmpEqual;
4461 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ONE: 4461 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ONE:
4462 return R == APFloat::cmpLessThan || R == APFloat::cmpGreaterThan; 4462 return R == APFloat::cmpLessThan || R == APFloat::cmpGreaterThan;
4463 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT: 4463 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
